It said President Jacob Zuma should: There is not sufficient appreciation of the fact that this is a national crisis and Zuma and his office should lead the thinking on resolutions the council declared. Access to higher education should not be the preserve of those who can afford it. It was deeply distressed by the proposed short-term funding levels. Our universities are a significant national priority. They are the only institutions that are capable of producing the high level skills that are required to advance innovation tackle the challenges of the 21st century and would affect the quality of research and learning. The fact that numerous universities are unable to continue with the 2016 academic programme has immense consequences for the country. The council stressed that stability had to return to the sector noting that the unfortunate but necessary and unavoidable presence of police on campus was a tragedy.